The paper deals with keyword search in relational databases, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of databases (cs.DB). The paper proposes algorithms for generating concise and informative Object Summaries (OSs) for a particular Data Subject (DS), which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the importance of selecting the most important tuples for the OS, which could be seen as a form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or machine learning (cs.LG).
